Description: Hard to Find- Ibanez RBM10 Reb Beach Stained Oil Signature Model Guitar The RBM10 is a Reb Beach series solid body electric guitar model introduced by Ibanez in 1994 and discontinued in 1995. Up for sale is the 1995 RBM10 which has a cedar body and stained oil finish. It is a signature model of American guitarist Reb Beach, who is best known for his work in the rock band “Winger”. The RBM10 was made in Korea by Cort. The body, which was designed by Reb himself, features a deep cutaway atthe back of the body all the way to the tremolo. It is also known as “Voyager”style. The 1995 RBM10 features a cedar body bolted to a maple neck with a 22-fret rosewood fingerboard with pearl dot position markers. Components include, Ibanez pickups with a humbucker at the bridge and single coil-sized humbuckers in the middle and neck positions. As well as, a double locking Lo- TRS II tremolo at the bridge. The RBM10 was discontinued along with the rest of the Reb Beach signature models after 1995. See below for Guitar specs. I purchased this guitar in 1995 and it has been in my collection on display and has only been played a handful of times by me. As such, this guitar has very minor “play” wear on the pick guard area. The body and the rest of the guitar are in flawless condition. This guitar is a beauty! Selling for $3,650. Since this guitar came stock with no case I will be packing it in multiple layers of bubble wrap in a bed of packing peanuts to ensure it arrives safe.
